Supreme Court — Appellate Term, November, 1899.

Before Freedman, P. J., MacLean and Leventritt, JJ.

William J. Walsh, Appellant, v. The Third Avenue Railroad Company, Respondent.— Apeal from a judgment in favor of the defendant, based on the verdict of a jury, rendered in the Municipal Court of the city of New York,, seventh district, borough of Manhattan. William J. Walsh (J. Campbell, Thompson, of counsel), for Appellant; Hoadly, Lauterbach & Johnson, for Respondent.

Judgment affirmed, with, costs to the respondent. No opinion*
